Static variable has an independent memory location or in other words, they have a single copy in memory.

They are not dependent on object.

As a result, when we are making change using a single object, the changes are getting reflected in other objects as 
well.

Because that specific variable is shared between all of these objects.

Static elements needs to be like accessed in a static method.

Simply make use of the name of the class dot name of your method and that's it.--> For--> Static 

Doubt?: public static class TestStaticTest {} invalid modifier - static 

